14},"Dashboards and chart visualizations","Architecture and development of microservices using Spring Boot and MongoDB for real-time security operations management. Implementation of a data aggregation layer with NodeJS and GraphQL, optimizing communication between the frontend and multiple backend services. Cloud infrastructure management on Azure with Kubernetes (AKS) and Docker, ensuring high availability and scalability. Rigorous application of SOLID principles and Agile methodologies (Scrum) under a Gitflow strategy, actively participating in code reviews and ensuring quality through automated testing with Gherkin.",[517,518],{"itemId":199,"itemValue":200},{"itemId":202,"itemValue":203},[520,521],{"itemId":206,"itemValue":98},{"itemId":208,"itemValue":209},[],[524,525],{"itemId":213,"itemValue":130},{"itemId":215,"itemValue":133},[527,528],{"itemId":218,"itemValue":152},{"itemId":220,"itemValue":221},[],[],[],[],[],[],{"itemId":185,"projectName":186,"role":536,"challenges":537,"department":194,"description":540,"end":196,"start":72,"tasks":541,"methodologies":543,"principles":546,"languages":547,"tools":550,"platforms":553,"collaborations":554,"incidents":555,"monitors":556,"libraries":557,"automations":558,"teamSize":276},"Frontend",[538,539],{"itemId":189,"itemValue":512},{"itemId":192,"itemValue":514},"We provide an hybrid app to allow security experts to register activities, monitor operations, and display statistics and sales feedback about any client or product, sold or installed. Technically talking it's an Ionic 3 + Angular 5 + Spring + MongoDB + CI\u002FCD project built with: - Microservices - Docker for the deployments (and local environments) - Everything deployed in Azure with Kubernetes as well as some On-Premise solutions (dev) - Acceptance testing using Gherkin sintax over Selenium and Appium with Python - Google Analytics for close-user evaluation - And one NodeJS service with GraphQL to aggregate and filter requests We're currently working usin